description: Application under Section 73 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 for variations to Conditions 9 (Parameter Plans), 10 (GEA Floorspace Limits), 34 (BREEAM) and 52 (Wind Mitigation) of part outline and part detail planning permission 2017/6762 dated 28th March 2019 for "Minor Material Amendment pursuant to Conditions 1 (time limit), 2 (time limit for reserved matters), 9 (parameter plans), 11 (Maximum Floorspaces), 15 (distribution and internal configuration of residential units for each plot), 32 (construction sequence and delivery plan) and 41 (land and groundwater contamination) of part outline and part detailed planning permission 2016/2424, dated 23rd January 2017 for "Minor Material Amendment pursuant to Conditions 3 (reserved matters), 9 (parameter plans), 10 (GEA floorspace limits), 13 (residential unit limit), 18 (car parking space limit), 32 (B8 use restriction) and 41 (land and groundwater contamination) of part outline and part detailed planning permission 2011/2462, dated 30/03/12 for demolition of all existing buildings and construction of a mixed use redevelopment comprising 7 building plots with buildings up to 23 storeys high to provide residential units; commercial and community floorspace; associated basement parking and part of the 'Nine Elms Linear Park'. All matters reserved apart from the appearance and scale of Blocks B1, D1 & G and two new access points from Nine Elms Lane." An addendum to the Environmental Statement has been submitted under The Town and Country Planning (Environmental Impact Assessment) Regulations 2017 (as amended)."
decision_conditions: Condition : 1 - Development was begun before the end of 5 years from the date of the original planning permission (ref: 2011/2462 dated 30/03/2012) as confirmed by letter dated 21 March 2017 from the London Borough of Wandsworth.
Condition : 2 - Submission of the first Reserved Matters within five years of the date of the original planning permission (ref: 2011/2462) was made on the 22nd March 2017 (ref: 2017/1766).

Condition : 3 - Approval of details of the following Reserved Matters shall be obtained from the Local Planning Authority in respect of each phase of the development (except where details are approved as part of this permission as noted below):
a)	the scale of the buildings and structures within the relevant plot (except for Plots B1, D1 and G) 
b)	the layout of the buildings, routes and structures
c)	access to and within the site for vehicles, cycles and pedestrians in accordance with the location of the access points shown on parameter plan NEP007 Rev. M
d)	the external appearance of the buildings and structures within the relevant plot (except for Plots B1, D1 and G), including facing materials  
e)	landscaping of private and public space (except for landscaping to Plot G).
Reason: To meet the requirements of The Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015.

Condition : 4 - Approval of the Reserved Matters referred to in Condition 3 shall be obtained from the Local Planning Authority in writing prior to the commencement of any part of the development to which those Reserved Matters relate (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation from taking place) and that part of the development shall be carried out only as approved.
Reason: To meet the requirements of The Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015.

Condition : 5 - No later than 8 years following the date of the original planning permission (ref. 2011/2462 dated 30/03/2012) an application or applications shall have been submitted to the Local Planning Authority for the approval of Reserved Matters in respect to all of the built accommodation hereby permitted. Reserved Matters applications for Plots B & D (ref 2017/6764 approved 29/03/2019), C1 (ref 2019/1696 approved 19/06/2019), E (ref 2019/2324), F & G (ref 2019/2325), the Linear Park (ref 2017/3526 approved 28/03/2018 and ref 2019/2269) and the access(s) (ref 2016/2329 approved 26/01/2017 and ref 2017/1766 approved 14/07/2017) have been submitted in accordance with this time limit. 
Reason: To prevent the accumulation of unimplemented planning permissions and to comply with Section 92 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended) and to meet the requirements of The Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015.

Condition : 6 - No Reserved Matters approval shall begin to be implemented more than 10 years from the date of the original planning permission (ref. 2011/2462 dated 30/03/2012) or 2 years from the date of the final approval of any Reserved Matters application, whichever is later. 
Reason: To prevent the accumulation of unimplemented planning permissions and to comply with Section 92 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended) and to meet the requirements of The Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015.

Condition : 7 - None of the works which are subject of the Reserved Matters details required in Condition 3 shall be commenced without the prior approval of those details by the Local Planning Authority
Reason: To meet the requirements of The Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015.

Condition : 8 - The Reserved Matters details submitted in relation to Condition 3 shall be in accordance with the elements in the Design Codes identified in this schedule and any subsequent reviews and updates to these documents.
Reason: To control the appearance and architectural form of the development and to ensure a high quality and co-ordinated design for the built form, in accordance with policy IS3 of the Core Strategy and policy DMS1 of the Development Management Policies Document.

Condition : 9 - The Reserved Matters details submitted in relation to Condition 3 shall be in accordance with the limitations set by the hereby approved parameter plans specified below and any drawings subsequently approved by Wandsworth Council as Local Planning Authority pursuant to any of the conditions in this decision letter: 
0591_PP-07_001 Rev G; 0591_PP-07_003 Rev M; 0591_PP-07_004 Rev K; 0591_PP-07_005 Rev M; 0591_PP-07_007 Rev M; 0591_PP-07_008 Rev L; 0591_PP-07_009 Rev L; 0591_PP-07_0010 Rev K; 0591_PP-07_011 Rev G; 0591_PP-07_012 Rev K; 0591_PP-07_013 Rev J; 0591_PP-07_014 Rev E; 0591_PP-07_015 Rev H; 0591_PP-07_016 Rev H; 0591_PP-07_017 Rev H; and 0591_M_03_100.
Reason: The merits and environmental impacts of the proposed development have been assessed in relation to the form of development shown on the submitted parameter plans.  In order to ensure the development proceeds on the basis of the scheme on which an Environmental Impact Assessment has been undertaken, the permission needs to be substantially tied to the details assessed in accordance with policy DMS1 of the Development Management Policies Document.

Condition : 10 - The total gross external floorspace areas of the uses hereby approved shall be limited to the following:
a) Overall gross external floorspace of all the uses, including parking, servicing, plant and storage, shall not exceed 226,910 sqm GEA (including 24,072sqm GEA of basement/podium level car parking, servicing, storage and plant)
b) Retail, Professional and Financial Services, Food and Drink uses (Classes A1/A2/A3/A4/A5), Community and Assembly and Leisure (Class D1 and D2) shall not exceed 9,658sqm GEA
c) Residential (Class C3) use shall not exceed 193,180sqm GEA.
Reason: to restrict the floorspace of the various uses to the levels proposed and assessed, and to ensure a suitable mix of uses within the development.

Condition : 11 - Subject to further restriction by other conditions attached to this planning permission, the maximum floorspace area in each Plot shall not exceed that set out in Table 1 of the Development Specification specified in this schedule.
Reason: To restrict the levels of floorspace of the various uses within the development to the Plot proposed to ensure a suitable mix, balance and distribution of uses throughout the development.

Condition : 12 - The distribution of uses within each Plot shall be in accordance with the parameter plans hereby approved. 
Reason: the impacts and the suitability of the various uses within the proposed development have been assessed in relation to their distribution across the site, as shown on the submitted parameter plans.  In order to ensure the development proceeds on the basis of the scheme on which the assessment has been undertaken, the permission needs to be substantially tied to the details assessed, and to allow the Local Planning Authority to review any potential changes to the scheme.

Condition : 13 - The residential (Class C3) accommodation hereby approved shall not exceed 1,950 units.
Reason: To control the number of residential units, to accord with the planning application, and to accord substantially with the number and mix of units set out in the Environmental Impact Assessment, and in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS5.

Condition : 14 - Prior to commencement of any Plot (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation from taking place), the private residential unit mix shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details as approved shall be implemented thereafter. A mix of unit sizes shall be provided in accordance with DMPD Policy DMH3 Adopted February 2012. The private residential unit mix for Plots B & D shall be in accordance with approval 2017/6786 dated 05/04/2019. The private residential unit mix for Plot C1 shall be in accordance with approval 2019/2899 dated 23/08/2019.  
Reason:  In accordance with Core Strategy policy IS5 and DMPD policy DMH3.

Condition : 15 - Details of the distribution and internal configuration of residential units for each Plot, including details of private gardens and amenity space, shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval in association with the Reserved Matters details required under Condition 3. Not less than 10% shall be wheelchair accessible or easily adaptable for wheelchair users (Building Regs. M4(3)) with the remaining 90% meeting Building Regs. M4(2).  The development shall not be implemented otherwise than in accordance with those details as approved. The distribution and internal configuration of residential units in Plot C1 shall be in accordance with approval 2019/1640 dated 29/07/2019.
Reason: To ensure satisfactory residential accommodation is provided, including for people with disabilities, in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS5 and DMPD policies DMH4, DMH6 and DMH7.

Condition : 16 - Unless otherwise provided by these conditions, the development hereby approved shall be carried out materially in accordance with the drawings and documents listed in this schedule. 
Reason: To ensure a satisfactory standard of development, and to allow the local planning authority to review any potential changes to the scheme.

Condition : 17 - The landscape works and planting for each Plot (with the exception of the Linear Park where details shall be submitted to and approved in writing prior to the commencement of any associated works) shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority prior to the completion of the superstructure works (e.g. concrete frame or any other such structural frame) and shall include details of habitat creation, a landscape management plan, external lighting, and species of new planting. The details as approved by the Local Planning Authority shall be carried out in accordance with a programme to be submitted to and agreed in writing with the Local Planning Authority. The landscaping associated with Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval 2017/6787 dated 29/07/2019. The landscaping associated with Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval 2019/1645 dated 16/07/2019 and 2020/1760 dated 22/07/2020.
Reason: In order that the landscaping is provided in co-ordination with the remainder of the development and to an appropriate timetable so that the areas of amenity space and public realm are provided in a timely fashion for the benefit of residents and the public and to ensure a satisfactory appearance of the development and ensure protection of wildlife and supporting habitat and secure opportunities for enhancement of the nature conservation value of the site, in accordance with Council policies DMS1 and DMO4.

Condition : 18 - The number of car parking spaces on the site shall not exceed 561 spaces or a ratio of 0.3 spaces per residential unit (whichever is the lower).  A minimum of 10% of all the car parking spaces on the site shall be suitable for the use of wheelchair users and permanently retained for persons with mobility disabilities. Any car parking provided as part of the approved development shall be provided prior to first occupation of the relevant Plot. 
Reason: To avoid creating unacceptable traffic congestion on the surrounding road network and ensure there would be adequate parking and servicing for the development and no adverse transport impacts from the development, and to ensure that adequate parking facilities for people with disabilities are provided and retained on site, in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS1 and DMPD policies DMT1 and DMT2.

Condition : 19 - The cycle parking levels provided on the site shall, as a minimum, be in line with Table T4 in Appendix 1 of the DMPD Adopted February 2012. Such cycle parking shall be provided prior to first occupation of the relevant Plot. 
Reason: To ensure an appropriate level of cycle parking is provided in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS1 and DMT2.

Condition : 20 - A Parking Management Strategy and Car Park Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of development of each Plot (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation taking place). This shall provide an overarching strategy for car park management for each Plot which will  include: pricing structure, means of separating public, operational and residential parking and enforcing that separation; allocation of residential spaces between market and affordable units; allocation of parking for people with disabilities; car club allocation; charging points for electric vehicles; cycle parking/storage differentiated by residential, public and other users; access controls to car parks; access controls to emergency vehicle routes; handling the relationship between private and service vehicles; a full delivery and servicing strategy for each Plot. The relevant Plot shall not be operated otherwise than in accordance with the associated Parking Management Strategy and Car Park Management Plan approved by the Council. The Parking Management Strategy and Car Park Management Plan for Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2017/6788 dated 03/09/2019. The Parking Management Strategy and Car Park Management Plan for Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/3305 dated 06/11/2019.
Reason: To ensure appropriate levels of parking are provided and adequate servicing arrangements and vehicle access, in line with council policy DMT2.

Condition : 21 - The management for all roads, including all pedestrian and cycle routes shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved under approval 2016/2577 dated 25/01/2017.
Reason: to ensure adequate access and servicing is maintained to the site and neighbouring sites in accordance with DMPD policy DMT2.

Condition : 22 - Details of electric vehicle car parking spaces shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority in association with the Reserved Matters to be submitted pursuant to Condition 3. Such details shall include provision of at least 20% active and 20% passive provision for all residential parking spaces and 10% active and 10% passive provision for all commercial uses. Such details as approved shall be implemented prior to first use of the car parking. The electric vehicle car parking spaces associated with Plots B & D shall be provided in accordance with approval ref. 2017/6789 dated 13/06/2019. The electric vehicle car parking spaces associated with Plot C1 shall be provided in accordance with approval ref. 2019/1646 dated 02/08/2019.
Reason: To ensure that adequate electric vehicle parking spaces are delivered and retained on site in accordance with policy 6.13 of the London Plan.

Condition : 23 - Details of ground and podium level cycle parking, including details of the area reserved for cycle hire schemes (in accordance with the associated S106 agreement) to be implemented associated with the relevant Plot on the development site shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of development of the relevant Plot (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation taking place). Such details as approved shall be implemented prior to first occupation of any part of the development of that Plot. The cycle parking associated with Plots B & D shall be provided in accordance with approval ref. 2017/6790 dated 29/05/2019. The cycle parking associated with Plot C1 shall be provided in accordance with approval ref. 2019/2998 dated 01/11/2019.
Reason: In the interests of the appearance of the development and to ensure an appropriate level of cycle parking is provided in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS1 and DMPD policy DMS1.

Condition : 24 - No individual Class A1, A2, A3, A4 or A5 unit shall exceed 300 sqm net sales area. 
Reason: To prevent large out-of-centre commercial units in accordance with Council policy DMTS2.

Condition : 25 - No more than 50% of the commercial units which are implemented pursuant to this planning permission shall be for any one particular A1, A2, A3, A4 or A5 use.
Reason: To prevent overconcentration of one particular use in the site in accordance with policy DMTS2.

Condition : 26 - Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015 or any replacement Order, no Class A2, A3, A4 or A5 floorspace implemented pursuant to this planning permission shall be used for Class A1 purposes.
Reason: To ensure an A1 use is not implemented without prior consideration by the Local Planning Authority in line with policy DMT2.

Condition : 27 - No A1, A2, A3, A4 or A5 unit that may be implemented subject to this planning permission shall be combined with an adjoining unit of a use class within category A of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015.
Reason: To prevent amalgamation of small units to create large out-of-centre units in line with policy DMTS2.

Condition : 28 - Details for each plot of the amount and spatial distribution of, and differentiation between Class A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, D1 and D2 uses within the areas shown to accommodate such uses in the parameter plans hereby approved, including details of size, location, fa�ade treatment and proposed forecourts, disabled access and toilets for each unit, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the first occupation of any unit in that Plot which is to be used for those purposes. The uses shall only be operated in accordance with the details thereby approved by the Local Planning Authority.
Reason: To ensure a suitable mix of uses within the development, in the interests of the appearance of the development and to ensure satisfactory access for people with disabilities in accordance with Council policies DMTS2, DMTS8 and DMS1.

Condition : 29 - Details of any external ventilation equipment, including ducting, shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval prior to installation and such equipment shall be installed in accordance with those details approved by the Local Planning Authority.
Reason: in the interests of local amenity and visual appearance, and in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS3.

Condition : 30 - The Class A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, D1 and D2 premises shall not be open to customers other than between 0700 and 2330, in respect of any individually defined unit pursuant to this condition.
Reason: to safeguard the amenities of the neighbourhood and local residents, in accordance with DMPD policy DMS1.

Condition : 31 - The A2 uses hereby approved shall not include use in connection with the hiring, distribution of or trading in motor vehicles, or in connection with driving instruction.
Reason: appropriate parking and service facilities are not provided for such uses in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS1 and DMPD policy DMT2.

Condition : 32 - Unless otherwise provided by these conditions, the development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with the Construction Sequence and Delivery Plan dated September 2016. Minor variations to this document may be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. 
Reason: To ensure a satisfactory standard of development and to allow the Local Planning Authority to review any potential changes to the scheme.

Condition : 33 - Prior to the commencement of development of each relevant Plot (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation taking place), and along with the Reserved Matters details required by Condition 3, details of sustainability and energy strategies for each Plot shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. These details shall include: BREEAM 2010, Code for Sustainable Homes (or equivalent), passive design measures, energy efficiency, and renewable technologies, and shall be accompanied by the District Heating Network Statement required to be submitted to the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of development of each Plot in line with the S106 attached to this planning permission. The sustainability and energy strategy details thereby approved shall be implemented prior to the first occupation of any part of the development of the relevant Plot. The sustainability and energy strategy for Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2017/6791 dated 09/08/2019. The sustainability and energy strategy for Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/1647 dated 28/06/2019.
Reason: to ensure the implementation of sustainable design, low carbon development and renewable energy in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS2 and DMPD policy DMS3.

Condition : 34 - Prior to the occupation of any commercial space within each relevant Plot, a Post Construction Certificate verifying that at least 'Very Good' BREEAM 2018 Level with a minimum score of 62% and all mandatory BREEAM 'Excellent' credits except for ENE01 for all commercial uses has been achieved, or such equivalent level that may be required to be met at the time of development through Building Regulations or other legislation, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.
Reason: to ensure the implementation of sustainable design, low carbon development and renewable energy in line with Core Strategy policy IS2 and DMPD policy DMS3.

Condition : 35 - For each Plot, details of the pneumatic waste system, or such alternative waste collection system as may be agreed with the Council to be installed, and the Sustainable Waste Strategy for the Plot, shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval in association with the Reserved Matters details required under Condition 3. The Sustainable Waste Strategy shall be informed by, and accompanied with, a feasibility study for the approved waste collection system to be submitted to the Local Planning Authority prior to commencement of development (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation taking place). The Sustainable Waste Strategy shall include details of the measures to ensure noise and smell from the approved waste collection system would be mitigated. The development of each Plot shall be implemented in accordance with those details approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and no part of that Plot shall be occupied prior to such approval. The Sustainable Waste Strategy for Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2017/6792 dated 19/07/2019. The Sustainable Waste Strategy for Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/1648 dated 27/06/2019. 
Reason: To mitigate the quantity of waste arising from the operation of the development, ensure appropriate provision is made for storage and disposal, and to minimise the environmental impacts from that waste in accordance with DMPD policy DMS1.

Condition : 37 - No development shall take place until the applicant has secured the implementation of a programme of archaeological work in accordance with a written scheme for investigation which has been submitted by the applicant and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The development shall only take place in accordance with the detailed scheme pursuant to this condition. The archaeological works shall be carried out by a suitably qualified investigating body acceptable to the Local Planning Authority. The programme of archaeological work associated with Phase 1 Works shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2017/5031 dated 05/10/2019. The programme of archaeological work associated with Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2017/6793 dated 11/04/2019. The programme of archaeological work associated with Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/2892 dated 23/08/2019.
Reason: in order that archaeological remains that may exist on the site can be investigated, in accordance with DMPD policy DMS2. This needs to be a pre-commencement condition as it deals with safeguards associated with archaeology.

Condition : 38 - Details of a scheme to protect the residential accommodation hereby approved from external noise sources, including details of fenestration, and balustrade and screen design to balconies and winter gardens, and details of ventilation, shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval for each Plot of development, prior to the completion of the superstructure works (e.g. concrete frame or any other such structural frame). The details for Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2020/1733 dated 22/07/2020. The scheme thereby approved by the Local Planning Authority shall be fully implemented prior to occupation of the residential accommodation to which it relates within that Plot.
Reason: to protect the occupiers or the residential buildings in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS4 and DMPD policy DMH4 (ii) and to ensure no conflict of use arises with nearby safeguarded wharves in accordance with Council policy PL9.

Condition : 39 - A Low Emission Strategy relating to each Plot during the operational phases shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the first occupation of any part of the relevant Plot. Each Plot shall be operated in accordance with the associated Low Emission Strategy as approved by the Local Planning Authority. 
Reason: To ensure the implementation of a low carbon development in line with Council policy IS2.

Condition : 40 - Details of a scheme to reduce or mitigate the adverse air quality impacts as identified in the Environmental Statement accompanying this planning application on the residential accommodation hereby approved, shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval with the Reserved Matters details required under Condition 3 for each Plot of the development. The scheme thereby approved by the Local Planning Authority shall be fully implemented prior to occupation of the residential accommodation to which it relates within that Plot. The air quality mitigation strategy associated with Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2017/7004 dated 04/07/2019. The air quality mitigation strategy associated with Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/1651 dated 23/07/2019.
Reason: to protect the occupiers or the residential buildings in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS4 and DMPD policy DMH4 (ii) and to ensure no conflict of use arises with nearby safeguarded wharves in accordance with Council policy PL9.

Condition : 41 - Prior to commencement of the relevant plot, the following components of a scheme to deal with the risks associated with contamination of the relevant Plot shall each be submitted to and approved, in writing, by the Local Planning Authority: 
i.	A preliminary risk assessment which has identified: 
o	All previous uses 
o	Potential contaminants associated with those uses 
o	A conceptual model of the site indicating sources, pathways and receptors 
o	Potentially unacceptable risks arising from contamination at the site 
ii.	A site investigation scheme, based on (1) to provide information for a detailed assessment of the risk to all receptors that may be affected, including those off site. 
iii.	The results of the site investigation and detailed risk assessment referred to in (2) and, based on these, an options appraisal and remediation strategy fiving full details of the remediation measures required and how they are to be undertaken. 
iv.	A verification plan providing details of the data that will be collected in order to demonstrate that the works set out in the remediation strategy in (3) are complete and identifying any requirements for contingency action. Any changes to these components require the express consent of the local planning authority. The scheme shall be implemented as approved. 
The works in relation to the site investigation and risk assessment for Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with application reference 2013/5518 dated 07/04/14. The works in relation to the remediation strategy for Phases 1 and 2 shall be undertaken in accordance with application reference 2014/3663 dated 14/08/14. The works relating to the site investigation and risk assessment and remediation method shall be undertaken in accordance with approval 2016/0350 dated 17/03/2016. The works relating to the Phase 1 Infrastructure Works shall be undertaken in accordance with application reference 2016/5696 dated 27/01/2017. The Verification Report for Phase 1 Remediatio

Condition : 42 - The development permitted by this planning permission shall only be carried out in accordance with the approved URS Flood Risk Assessment (ref: 49316105 dated May 2011) and the following mitigation measures detailed within the FRA: 
i.	The majority of the residential uses are to be set above the maximum 1 in 200-year flood level on site, as derived through breach analysis (4.85m AOD) plus 300mm freeboard. Where this can not be achieved as shown on the layout plans submitted for this outline application and included within the FRA, all sleeping accommodation must be set at first floor level or above. 
ii.	Prior to commencement of development of each Plot a flood management plan shall be produced and submitted to the Local Planning Authority in accordance with the FRA recommendations for approval and implementation. This shall identify and make provision for safe route(s) or safe refuge areas within the building for occupants to use during times of flood. 
iii.	All ground floor basement uses shall be constructed with flood proofing or resilience measures and the basements shall be fully tanked to prevent any water ingress. 
The flood management plan required under part (ii) of this condition associated with Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2018/0410 dated 03/06/2019. The flood management plan required under part (ii) of this condition associated with Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/3304 dated 10/09/2019. 
Reason: To minimise the risk of internal flooding to property and to ensure the safety of occupants during a flood, to ensure users of the site are aware of how to act during times of flood to minimise risk and to ensure no additional burden on the emergency services and to prevent the services to the building being cut off during a flood, in accordance with DMPD policy DMS5.

Condition : 43 - Prior to commencement of development of the relevant Plot (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation taking place), a detailed surface water drainage scheme shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Such a scheme shall include Greenfield runoff rates (no more than 46l/sec) for the proposed development within the relevant Plot and all the SUDS features set out in the URS Flood Risk Assessment (ref: 49316105 dated May 2011) and accompanying Drainage Strategy (Appendix D of the FRA) such as balancing ponds, swales, green and brown roofs, permeable paving and storage tanks. The details hereby approved shall be implemented and maintained thereafter prior to first occupation of any part of the development of that Plot. The surface water drainage scheme associated with Haines Street & Moat Street shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2016/2331 dated 02/02/2017. The surface water drainage scheme associated with the Phase 1 Infrastructure Works shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2016/5449 dated 06/02/2017. The surface water drainage scheme associated with Phase 1 Linear Park shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2017/3617 dated 26/09/2017. The surface water drainage scheme associated with Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/1458 dated 29/05/2019. The surface water drainage scheme associated with Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/3384 dated 12/09/2019.
Reason: To ensure a sustainable drainage system is implemented and to minimise the risk of flooding from the drainage system and, to improve habitat and amenity in accordance with Council policies DMS5 and DMS6.

Condition : 44 - No infiltration of surface water drainage into the ground is permitted other than with the express written consent of the Local Planning Authority, which may be given for those parts of the site where it has been demonstrated that there is no resultant unacceptable risk to Controlled Waters. The development shall be carried out in accordance with any details approved as part of such consent.
Reason: Infiltrating water has the potential to cause remobilisation of contaminants present in shallow soil/made ground which could ultimately cause pollution of groundwater, to prevent pollution in accordance with council policy IS4.

Condition : 45 - Details of school pick up and drop off areas, including location and details of management, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority in association with the Reserved Matters details required by Condition 3 for Plot C2 identified on the drawings specified in the schedule. The details thereby approved shall be implemented and permanently retained for the prescribed uses prior to first occupation of any part of Plot C2.
Reason: to ensure appropriate facilities are provided and retained on site, in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS1 and DMPD policy DMT2.

Condition : 46 - The window glass of the shopfronts hereby approved shall not be mirrored, painted or be otherwise obscured. No shelving, cabinets or other such obstruction shall be placed at any time within 1m of the shop windows fronting a road or footpath.
Reason: In order to prevent the creation of a dead frontage and to ensure an appropriate the character and appearance of the streetscene, in accordance with policy DMTS8 and DMS1 of the DMPD submission version.

Condition : 47 - Prior to occupation of any commercial unit in each Plot, details of any outside forecourt/outdoor space associated with any of those units shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Such details shall include the location, hours of use and any boundary treatment (temporary or permanent). The forecourt/outdoor spaces shall only be implemented in accordance with the details approved prior to first occupation of the relevant commercial unit within that Plot. 
Reason: In the interests of the appearance of the development, the amenity of neighbouring residential properties and to ensure there is no street clutter in line with council policies DMS1, appearance and amenity and ensure not impact pedestrian/cycle movement.

Condition : 48 - Prior to the first occupation of any residential units within each Plot, details of the proposed boundary treatment to the private communal gardens and private gardens shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority. The details thereby approved shall be implemented prior to the occupation of the residential units within each Plot. 
Reason: To ensure a satisfactory appearance and to protect the privacy of future occupiers and to accord with council policy DMS1.

Condition : 49 - Notwithstanding any material specified in the application documents hereby approved, details and samples of materials proposed to be used on all external surfaces of each Plot shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of development of the relevant Plot (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation taking place). The development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved materials and details. The materials associated with Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2017/6795 dated 03/09/2019. The materials associated with Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with ref. 2019/3326 dated 26/11/2019.
Reason: in order to assess the suitability of the proposed materials, in the interests of the appearance on the locality, in accordance with Council policy DMS1.

Condition : 50 - Prior to the fit out of the A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, D1 or D2 uses in the relevant Plot, details of noise insulation measures to provide effective resistance to the transmission of airborne and impact sound between any A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, D1 or D2 uses and any residential uses (C3) shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The approved details shall be implemented prior to the commencement of the A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, D1 or D2 uses within the relevant Plot. 
Reason: To safeguard the amenities of adjoining occupiers, in accordance with Council policy DMH4.

Condition : 51 - Facing residential windows within Plots B and D shall be a minimum of 18m apart.
Reason: To safeguard the amenities of residential occupiers within the development, in accordance with Council policy DMH4.

Condition : 52 - Details of mitigation against any strong wind impact identified in the Environmental Statement submitted with this planning application shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority in association with the Reserved Matters details in Condition 3 for the Plot where that impact is identified. The development of that Plot shall be implemented in accordance with such details as approved by the Local Planning Authority. The wind mitigation measures associated with Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2017/6796 dated 29/07/2019. The wind mitigation measures associated with Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/1650 dated 27/06/2019. 
Reason: In accordance with DMPD policy DMS4.

Condition : 53 - No impact piling at any Plot shall take place until a piling method statement for that Plot (detailing the type of piling to be undertaken and the methodology by which such piling will be carried out, including measures to prevent and minimise the potential for damage to subsurface water or sewerage infrastructure, and the programme for the works) has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority in consultation with the relevant water or sewerage undertaker. Any piling must be undertaken in accordance with the terms of the approved piling method statement. Piling associated with Plot C1 shall only be undertaken in accordance with approval ref. 2019/3251 dated 12/09/2019.
Reason: The proposed works will be in close proximity to underground water and sewerage utility infrastructure and is therefore necessary to safeguard against the potential to impact on local underground water and sewerage utility infrastructure in accordance with Council policy DMS1.

Condition : 54 - Prior to commencement of development of the relevant Plot (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation taking place) impact studies of the existing water supply infrastructure shall be submitted to, and approved in writing by, the Local Planning Authority (in consultation with Thames Water) in relation to that Plot. The studies should determine the magnitude of any new additional capacity required in the system and suitable connection point. Development of Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2018/6058 dated 10/04/2019. Development of Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/2897 dated 23/08/2019. 
Reason: To ensure that the water supply infrastructure has sufficient capacity to cope with the additional demand in accordance with Council policy DMS1.

Condition : 55 - Should Wind Turbines and/or Photovoltaic cells be proposed as part of the development of any Plot, full details shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, having taken account of relevant statutory consultees, prior to installation. The details shall be implemented as approved. 
Reason: To ensure the development does not endanger the safe movement of aircraft or the operation of Heathrow Airport through interference with communication, navigational aids and surveillance equipment.

Condition : 56 - Prior to first occupation of each Plot, a Development Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority which shall include details of how the hereby approved development will be managed and maintained and shall include security measures; management procedures; tenant forums/complaint procedures; maintenance charges. The Development Management Plan shall thereafter be implemented as approved.
Reason: To ensure a satisfactory management of the development in accordance with Council policy DMS4.

Condition : 57 - The noise levels from any installed plant/equipment shall be at least 10dB(A) below the existing background measurement (LA90) (expressed in dB(A)) when measured or calculated at a point one metre external to the nearest residential or school facades when all plant/equipment are in operation.
Reason: In the interests of residential amenity in line with policies DMH4 and DMC2.

Condition : 58 - A Servicing and Delivery Management Plan associated with each Plot shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the occupation of the Plot to which the Plan relates. The Servicing and Delivery Management Plan shall thereafter be implemented as approved.  
Reason: to ensure suitable strategy for servicing and delivering to all uses within the scheme can be achieved in accordance with DMPD policies DMT2 and DMH4.

Condition : 59 - Prior to the commencement of development for each Plot (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation from taking place) up-to-date phasing plan(s) shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and development shall not be carried out other than in accordance with such approved phasing plan(s). Development of Plots B & D shall be in accordance with approval ref. 2018/5175 dated 29/11/2018. Development of Plot C1 shall be in accordance with approval ref. 2019/3143 dated 23/08/2019.
Reason: To ensure a satisfactory standard of development and having regard to the illustrative nature of the phasing plans, reference 'CIL Phasing Plan August 2016' and 'Sequence and Delivery: September 2016' approved under application 2016/2424 dated 12/01/2017.

Condition : 60 - Each Plot shall achieve a maximum water use of 105 litres per person per day (plus 5 litres for outside use) in line with the Water Efficiency Calculator for new dwellings from the Department of Communities and Local Government. Prior to first occupation of any residential unit within a Plot, evidence to demonstrate that the internal water consumption of that Plot will not exceed 105l/p/day shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Measures integrated shall be retained in good working order for the lifetime of the development.
Reason: In the interests of sustainable development in accordance with Council policies IS2 and DMS3.

Condition : 61 - The development hereby approved shall achieve a minimum of a 35% reduction in CO2 emissions below the maximum threshold set in Building Regulations Part L 2013. Within three months of the first occupation of any Plot, evidence (e.g. photographs, copies of installation contracts and as-built worksheets prepared under SAP or the National Calculation Method) shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority demonstrating that the development has achieved at least a 35% reduction in CO2 emissions below the maximum threshold set in Building Regulations Part L 2013.
Reason: In the interests of sustainable development in accordance with Council policies IS2 and DMS3.

Condition : 62 - Prior to first occupation of each Plot, a verification report demonstrating completion of the works set out in the approved remediation strategy and the effectiveness of the remediation shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The report shall include results of sampling and monitoring carried out in accordance with the approved verification plan to demonstrate that the site remediation criteria have been met. It shall also include any plan (a 'long-term monitoring and maintenance plan') for longer-term monitoring of pollutant linkages, maintenance and arrangements for contingency action, as identified in the verification plan, if appropriate, and for the reporting of this to the Local Planning Authority. Any long-term monitoring and maintenance plan shall be implemented as approved.
Reason: To prevent any pollution in accordance with Core Strategy policy IS4.

Condition : 63 - Build to Rent units within Plots B & D shall be provided with access to the shared amenity spaces as indicated on the plans identified in the schedule above to residents of that Plot or Plots in perpetuity. 
Reason: To ensure a satisfactory appearance and adequate living conditions for future occupiers in accordance with Council Policy DMS1.

Condition : 64 - Build to Rent units within Plots B & D shall provide a minimum of 3,141sqm (GEA) of internal amenity space and 4,000sqm (GEA) of external amenity space and is to be retained in perpetuity.
Reason: To ensure a satisfactory appearance and adequate living conditions for future occupiers in accordance with Council Policy DMS1.

Condition : 65 - Prior to commencement of the relevant Plot (except that this shall not prevent works of site clearance, demolition of existing buildings and structures, ground investigation and site survey works, erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding, archaeological investigation and works of decontamination and remediation taking place), the following information shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority:
-      Location and type of bird, bat and invertebrate boxes on roofs;
-      Plans and cross-sections to show green/brown roofs with wildflower seed mix, varying substrate depth between 70-150mm and log piles; and,
-      Planting of native shrub species to attract birds and invertebrates on accessible roofs
The development shall be implemented in accordance with the details thereby approved prior to first occupation of the development of that Plot. Development of Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2018/6059 dated 09/08/2019. Development of Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval ref. 2019/3387 dated 09/10/2019.
Reason: To ensure that the biodiversity value of the borough will be protected and enhanced for the benefit of people Policy PL4.

Condition : 66 - All Non Road Mobile Machinery (NRMM) of net power of 37kW and up to and including 560kW used during the course of the demolition, site preparation and construction phases of the development shall comply with the emission standards set out in Chapter 7 of the GLA's Supplementary Planning Guidance 'Control of Dust and Emissions During Construction and Demolition' dated July 2014 (SPG) or any subsequent guidance. 
Reason: To achieve appropriate sustainability standards in accordance with policy DMS3 and in accordance with London Plan policies 5.3 and 7.14.

Condition : 67 - The external lighting associated with Plots B & D shall be implemented in accordance with approval 2019/5241 dated 15/01/2020 prior to first occupation of the relevant Plot. The external lighting associated with Plot C1 shall be implemented in accordance with approval 2020/1107 dated 14/05/2020 prior to first occupation. 
Reason: In the interests of the appearance of the development and the amenity of neighbouring properties in accordance with policy DMS1.

Condition : 68 - The taxi pick-up/drop-off shall be implemented in accordance with approval 2018/6057 dated 19/07/2019 prior to first occupation of the development and retained thereafter for the lifetime of the development for use only as a taxi pick-up/drop-off. 
Reason: In the interests of highway safety and of the maximisation of opportunities for travel by sustainable modes of transport in accordance with Policy DMT1 and DMT2.

Condition : 69 - Prior to the occupation of any commercial space within each relevant Plot, a Refurbishment and Fit-out Certificate verifying that at least 'Excellent' BREEAM 2018 Level for all commercial uses has been achieved, or such equivalent level that may be required to be met at the time of development through Building Regulations or other legislation, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. 
REASON: to ensure the implementation of sustainable design, low carbon development and renewable energy in line with Core Strategy Policy IS2 and DMPD Policy DMS3.

Condition : 70 - Any takeaway food deliveries associated with the A3/A5 use(s) hereby approved within Plots E, F or G shall not be undertaken by motorised scooter.
REASON: Appropriate parking facilities are not provided for such uses, and to protect nearby residents' amenity, in accordance with Core Strategy Policy IS1 and DMPD Policies DMS1 and DMT2.

Condition : 71 - INFORMATIVE: In dealing with this application the Council has implemented the requirement in the National Planning Policy Framework 2019 to work with the applicant in a positive and proactive manner and the Council has, as far as practicable, sought solutions to problems arising in relation to dealing with the planning application.  The Council has made available detailed advice in the form of its statutory policies in the Local Plan consisting of the Core Strategy, Development Management Policies Document, Supplementary Planning Documents and where appropriate the Site Specific Allocations Document as well as offering a full pre-application advice service, in order to ensure that the applicant has been given every opportunity to submit an application which is likely to be considered favourably. In addition, where appropriate, further guidance was offered to the applicant during the processing of the application.

Condition : 72 - INFORMATIVE: In arriving at its decision, the local planning authority has taken into consideration environmental information pursuant to the Town and Country Planning (Environmental Impact Assessment) Regulations 2017.

Condition : 73 - INFORMATIVE: Community Infrastructure Levy (CIL): From the information available, it appears that the development permitted is subject to a Community Infrastructure Levy charge in accordance with the Community Infrastructure Levy Regulations 2010 (as amended) (the "Regulations"). 
You or the relevant interested parties are required to provide the Council with the information set out in the Regulations. This process for the collection of CIL includes:  the requirement to complete an "Assumption of Liability" form as soon as possible;  in order to claim charitable exemption or social housing relief or other forms of relief you or the relevant interested party should also complete a "Claiming Exemption or Relief" form. 
The Council will, if appropriate, then issue a Liability Notice(s) which details the charges due. As soon as the developer, landowner or other interested party(ies) is aware of the date when development is going to start they must also submit a "Commencement Notice".  Failure to comply with the Regulations, including failure to complete the forms when required or providing inaccurate information can lead to surcharges or other penalties as set out in the Regulations. It can also mean that any exemptions or reliefs are lost.
General information on the Community Infrastructure Levy, including the forms mentioned above can be found on the Planning Portal (www.planningportal.gov.uk). Details of the Mayoral CIL can be found on the GLA and TfL websites (www.london.gov.uk and www.tfl.gov.uk). The Assumption of Liability Form, Claiming of Exemption or Relief Form and Commencement Notice must be sent to: Community Infrastructure Levy Environment and Community Services Wandsworth Council Town Hall London SW18 2PU cil@wandsworth.gov.uk Fax: 020 8871 6003 (marked FAO CIL)

Condition : 74 - INFORMATIVE: Any assessment of CIL liability by the Council has been based on the information provided. The assessment of CIL liability referred to in this informative is indicative only and is not intended to provide a binding estimate of the actual CIL liability likely to be incurred.  The assessment of the actual CIL liability will be provided pursuant to and in accordance with the Community Infrastructure Levy Regulations 2010 (as amended).  Where the calculation of CIL liability includes taking account of the existing use of a building, CIL liability may change if the information provided in relation to the existing use(s) of buildings, is not still current at the time of the decision which first permits development.

Condition : 75 - INFORMATIVE: This planning permission qualifies as a phased permission, which expressly provides for the development to be carried out in phases for the purposes of the Community Infrastructure Levy Regulations 2010 (as amended).

Condition : 76 - INFORMATIVE: With regard to surface water drainage it is the responsibility of a developer to make proper provision for drainage to ground, water courses or a suitable sewer. In respect of surface water it is recommended that the applicant should ensure that storm flows are attenuated or regulated into the receiving public network through on or off site storage. When it is proposed to connect to a combined public sewer, the site drainage should be separate and combined at the final manhole nearest the boundary. Connections are not permitted for the removal of groundwater. Where the developer proposes to discharge to a public sewer, prior approval from Thames Water Developer Services will be required to ensure that the surface water discharge from the site shall not be detrimental to the existing sewerage system. They can be contacted on 0800 009 3921.

Condition : 77 - INFORMATIVE: Thames Water advise that the proposal should incorporate flood protection measures, for example non-return valve (or other suitable device), to avoid the risk of sewer backflow at a later date, on the assumption that the sewerage network may surcharge to ground level during storm conditions.

Condition : 78 - INFORMATIVE: Thames Water recommends the installation of a properly maintained fat trap on all catering establishments. We further recommend, in line with best practice for the disposal of Fats, Oils and Grease, the collection of waste oil by a contractor, particularly to recycle for the production of bio diesel. Failure to implement these recommendations may result in this and other properties suffering blocked drains, sewage flooding and pollution to local watercourses. Further information on the above is available in a leaflet, 'Best Management Practices for Catering Establishments' which can be requested by telephoning 0203 577 9963 or found at https://www.nwl.co.uk/_assets/documents/FOG_A4_12_page.pdf)

Condition : 79 - INFORMATIVE: Where a developer proposes to discharge groundwater into a public sewer, a groundwater discharge permit will be required. Groundwater discharges typically result from construction site dewatering, deep excavations, basement infiltration, borehole installation, testing and site remediation. Groundwater permit enquiries should be directed to Thames Water's Risk Management Team by telephoning 020 8507 4890 or by emailing wwqriskmanagement@thameswater.co.uk. Application forms should be completed on line via www.thameswater.co.uk/wastewaterquality. Any discharge made without a permit is deemed illegal and may result in prosecution under the provisions of the Water Industry Act 1991.

Condition : 80 - INFORMATIVE: Network Rail request that the developer contacts its Asset Protection Wessex team and its Territory Asset Protection Engineer at: AssetProtectionWessex@networkrail.com prior to any development/construction works. A Development Questionnaire and an Asset Protection Agreement (APA) will need to be signed submitted to Network Rail Asset Protection (ASPRO) protection team prior to any works commencing on site. In the interest of the protection of Network Rail asset and train operation the developer should also carry out and submit to Network Rail:
a)	site investigation that fully categorises site conditions over the full extent of the site;
b)	traffic incursion risk assessment due to position of school building on Plot C2;
c)	lifting plan for all lifting adjacent to Network Rail land; and
d)	RAMS for all works adjacent to Network Rail infrastructure.
The developer should also ensure:
e)	the development complies with Networks Rail's standard advice and requirements for safe operations of the railway and the protection of Network Rail's adjoining land which includes future maintenance, drainage, plant and materials, scaffolding, piling, fencing, lighting, noise and vibration and landscaping; and 
f)	the proposal, both during construction and after completion of works on site does no encroach on Network Rail land; affect the safety, operation or integrity of the company's railway and its infrastructure; undermine its support zone; damage the company's infrastructure; place additional load on cuttings; adversely affect any railway land or structure; over-sail or encroach upon the air-space of any Network Rail land; or cause to obstruct or interfere with any works or proposed works or Network Rail development both now and in the future.

Condition : 81 - INFORMATIVE: Notes for Condition 66:
All major development sites in Greater London and all sites within the Central Activity Zone shall keep an inventory on site and on the online register at: https://nrmm.london/ of all NRMM between 37kW and 560kW. All NRMM shall meet Stage IIIA of EU Directive 97/68/EC (as amended) as a minimum within Greater London (Stage IIIB from 1st September 2020) and Stage IIIB of EU Directive 97/68/EC as a minimum within the Central Activity Zone (Stage IV from 1st September 2020).
